\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. E. pumilio} (Portenschl.) A. DC. in DC.,{\i  Prodr.} {\b 7}: 449 (1839). Stems 1-3 cm, ascending to erect, densely leafy, simple. Leaves (0·5-)8-20(-25) × 1(-2) mm, linear, sessile. Bracts subovate-lanceolate, linear-attenuate, shorter than the flowers, ciliate, hirsute above. Flowers solitary, sessile. Ovary glabrous; calyx-teeth lanceolate, 11/2-2 times as long as the ovary, sparsely hirsute, not appendiculate. Corolla (11-)14-18(-24) mm, blue-violet, rarely white, glabrous or very rarely sparsely and shortly hirsute on the veins. •{\i  W. Jugoslavia} ({\i Biokovo Planina}). Ju.
