\pard\f0\fs28  Very variable, though apparently with little geographical or ecological differentiation. Subsp.{\b  echinata} (Boiss. & Reuter) Rivas Martinez, {\i Publ. Inst. Biol. Apl.} ({\i Barcelona}){\b  42}: 122 (1967) is a fairly well-marked variant occurring in S.E. Spain and perhaps S. Italy and Sicilia. It is a large, robust, white-hispid plant, with involucral bracts with thickened margins. In other parts of the range of the species the correlation between these characters breaks down, so it does not seem possible to maintain it at subspecific rank.
