\pard\f0\fs28  A small, annual variant from S. Spain, with thickened leaf-margins, long involucral bracts and ciliate calyx-teeth has been described as {\b J. blepharodon} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Pugillus }72 (1852). It is connected by numerous intermediates with typical{\i  J. montana,} and also has 2n = 12.
